<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}+{7}{y}={49}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}-{6}{y}=-{99}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --9. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{9}}{{1}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{9}}}{{1}}{\left({1}{x}+{7}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{9}}}{{1}}{\left({49}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{9}\right)}{x}+{63}{y}={441}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}-{6}{y}=-{99}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{57}{y}={342}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{342}}{{57}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{7}{\left({6}\right)}={49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{\left({42}\right)}={49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}={49}-{\left({42}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{7}}{{1}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>